# SECURITY: keep secrets and local artifacts out of image layers.
# `COPY . .` in the Dockerfile would otherwise bake the build context
# (including a populated .env with SECRET_KEY, LND macaroon, DB/Redis
# passwords, gateway token) into a root-owned layer, bypassing on-disk
# 0600 perms. See internal_docs/security_review_2026-06-20_remediation_plan.md (H4).

# Secrets / credentials
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.macaroon
*.key
*.pem
*.crt
*-backup-*.txt
secrets/
tor-proxy/*.cookie

# VCS / history
.git
.gitignore
.git-blame-ignore-revs

# Local / internal planning + references (never shipped)
internal_docs/
references/
builds/

# Rust build output (not needed in the Python app image). Cargo.lock is NOT
# ignored — Dockerfile.gateway needs it for a reproducible gateway build, and the
# Python app image never COPYs it (so it costs nothing there).
target/

# Python / build caches
agent_wallet.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage*
htmlcov/

# Node
scripts/node_modules/
node_modules/

# Logs / scratch
*.log
*.tmp
